From 0a8ca26ba20bdfdfccb79a4821aa0bad8ff9529c Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Sriram Sankar Sankarapandian Thangaraj <sriramsa@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Fri, 1 Aug 2025 11:48:47 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] UPSTREAM:PROTOCOL:hostapd:Fix radius mem corruption

radius_das_open_port() allocates memory using
os_zalloc() but the same memory is freed directly
by free() causing memory corruption.

Fixed by replacing free() call with os_free()

Fixes: openwrt_patches/761-shared_das_port.patch

Patch-dependency: openwrt_patches/761-shared_das_port.patch
Patch-work: None
---
 src/radius/radius_das.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/src/radius/radius_das.c b/src/radius/radius_das.c
index 5d0c88a..1972288 100644
--- a/src/radius/radius_das.c
+++ b/src/radius/radius_das.c
@@ -622,7 +622,7 @@ static void radius_das_close_port(struct radius_das_port *p)
 	dl_list_del(&p->list);
 	eloop_unregister_read_sock(p->sock);
 	close(p->sock);
-	free(p);
+	os_free(p);
 }
 
 struct radius_das_data *
-- 
2.34.1

